    "See Section 5.3.3 of the main text for further details.",
    "(b) Negative Labels",
    "In recent work, Sarkar and Vafa (2024) show LLMs used to predict a future outcome from some text can inadvertently draw on information from the time of the outcome rather than the time of the text.",
    "The authors refer to this as \"look-ahead bias,\" which violates our \"no training leakage\" condition.",
    "See also Glasserman and Lin (2023)."
